						               													<description>Hostile Environment: Special Forces is a fast-paced tactical 28mm miniatures game that is designed to be played on a battle mat with a 1&amp;rdquo; grid. The game is based on the Hostile Environment world, but players may use whatever modern or futuristic miniatures they have from Vietnam, Cold War or Science Fiction eras.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Hostile Environment uses a die-pull initiative system to keep players on their toes. Better soldiers get greater odds of more activations, but lesser soldiers are allowed more numbers to keep fights balanced.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each miniature represents a single unit ranging in skill from green to elite. There are over 15 different weapon types and 6+ armor types from modern weapons and armor to alt-future tech.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Most matches take about 90 minutes using at most two dozen miniatures.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;H.E.: Special Forces can be played solo, using the Hostile Tactical AI card deck (sold separately).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2050, the world has entered total chaos. P68P, a poisonous pollen has killed over a billion people, while the toxic gnidia plant, once bred in labs, continues to spread like wildfire. Governments that once ruled humanity have fallen into darkness.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;ldquo;The Great Wipe,&amp;rdquo; a hacker attack by the Red 76&amp;rsquo;ers in 2038 has virtually erased the internet. Now, only a few left have the knowledge to bring back the sciences that have been forgotten. Only the READ, a source of collective consciousness, allows mankind to share information. But, Paven the creator of &amp;ldquo;the language of God,&amp;rdquo; rules from the grave, spreading his mesmerism into weaker minds, leaving the zombies to his controlling thoughts.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Failure of silver, the nano blood that cured cancer and heart disease has left mankind grappling with age old viruses thought to be extinct. Scarmine Lab&amp;rsquo;s mercenaries formed a special force of Population Insurance Tactics (PIT) to find humans that can still create antibodies that have become dormant in most humans.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All that is left of the world is a Hostile Environment.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
